BFN 

  [Text] Hassan Mohamed Nur Qalaad, a member of the Popular 
Defense Committee, has reported on the security situation of 
Mogadishu Airport. Mr. Qalaad and other officials, who were on 
a working tour to check security at important sites including 
Mogadishu Airport and its surroundings, said the security of 
these areas was very good and there was no problem whatsoever. 
The officials, who included Khalif Dhunkaal and Abdulahi Shire 
Ugas, alias Anabodhe, said that Mogadishu Airport was for all 
Somali people and was important for social work. Therefore, its 
security had been fully guaranteed. They added that social work 
had started at the airport and no insecurity was observed. 
Flights from Mogadishu Airport had now begun properly. 
  Finally, the officials called on Somali people in general, 
and those living in Mogadishu city in particular, to be calm and 
participate in the reconstruction of their country. 

